by its regulator the federal housing finance agency based on the banks financial information at june   about the bank the federal home loan bank of boston is a cooperatively owned wholesale bank for housing finance in the six new england states its mission is to provide highly reliable wholesale funding and liquidity to its member financial institutions in new england the bank also develops and delivers competitively priced financial products services and expertise that support housing finance community development and economic growth including programs targeted to lowerincome households federal home loan bank of boston balance sheet highlights dollars in thousands unaudited    assets advances       investments     mortgage loans held for portfolio net    other assets    total assets       liabilities consolidated obligations net       deposits    mandatorily redeemable capital stock    other liabilities    capital class b capital stock    retained earnings  unrestricted    retained earnings  restricted     total retained earnings    accumulated other comprehensive loss    total capital    total liabilities and capital       total regulatory capitaltoassets ratio       ratio of market value of equity mve to par value of capital stock        income statement highlights dollars in thousands unaudited for the three months ended for the nine months ended      total interest income           total interest expense      net interest income      net interest income after provision for credit losses      net otherthantemporary impairment losses oninvestment securities recognized in income      litigation settlements —  —   other loss      operating expense      other expense      ahp assessment      net income           performance ratios  return on average assets           return on average equity            net interest spread           net interest margin              for additional information on the banks capital requirements see item  — managements discussion and anal